1. Thirty explosive athletes performed tests.
2. The tests included a back squat for one repetition maximum (1RM) strength.
3. The tests also included complex training bouts.
4. The purpose of the tests was to determine the individual optimal timing of PAP.
5. The tests also aimed to determine the height and peak power of a counter movement jump.
6. The tests were performed before and after supplementation.
